title: VIDEO OF THE WEEK: Benedict Cumberbatch has no political ambitions after Black Mass role
text:
Sherlock star Benedict Cumberbatch has revealed playing a politician in his latest film has not whetted his appetite to pursue any political aspirations. Share article 
Cumberbatch portrays William "Billy" Bulger the law-abiding brother of Boston mobster and FBI informant James "Whitey" Bulger in Black Mass, which premiered at the Odeon Leicester Square as part of the BFI London Film Festival.
